metadata.name: Neptune's Agony V.1
metadata.description: "Neptune's Agony" is a mixed media painting (oil, acrylic, etc. on canvas). Neptune is the "god of seas" in Greek mythology. The painting is brought to life with visual effects to induce the real drama and agony felt by the artist Negin Taghavi inspired by sculptor Lambert-Sigisbert Adam. The actual painting is 80cm in diameter.
